After doing some math (e.g.
 solving all static optimization problems, normalizing non-stationary BGPs
 by 
\begin_inset Formula $\overline{q}$
\end_inset

 and rewriting in stationary form, etc.), we can say that an equilibrium
 is defined by a set of functions and numbers satisfying certain conditions.
 These are summarized below:
\end_layout

